WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:30.999
STOCK EXCHANGE PALACE
CROATIAN NATIONAL BANK BUILDING

00:00:33.999 --> 00:00:38.999
This impressive building
at Hrvatskih Velikana Square

00:00:38.999 --> 00:00:42.999
houses the Croatian National Bank
which was opened on 18 June 1927

00:00:43.320 --> 00:00:48.999
as the Palace of the Zagreb
Stock and Commodity Exchange.

00:01:02.999 --> 00:01:09.160
In 1907, the Commodities and
Stocks Section was established.

00:01:09.999 --> 00:01:14.000
MIRA KOLAR-DIMITRIJEVIĆ, PhD
historian

00:01:14.640 --> 00:01:17.999
It was sometimes called the
Exchange, but documents show

00:01:18.160 --> 00:01:20.999
that it was actually called

00:01:20.999 --> 00:01:24.480
the Section for Trading in
Commodities and Stocks.

00:01:25.999 --> 00:01:31.999
Initially, brokers gathered
in the Grand Café here.

00:01:31.999 --> 00:01:36.999
A few years later they moved to a
new trading house in Jurišić Street

00:01:36.999 --> 00:01:42.999
and then again in 1921 to an even
larger rented office in Hatz Street.

00:01:43.999 --> 00:01:46.960
Many people saw themselves
getting rich with a fortune

00:01:46.999 --> 00:01:51.160
to provide for them for the rest
of their lives, newspapers wrote.

00:01:51.640 --> 00:01:55.999
They were always talking about
making one more final transaction

00:01:55.999 --> 00:02:00.800
before quitting the slippery slope
that the stock exchange was.

00:02:00.999 --> 00:02:05.960
And it was this very last trade
that would cost them their fortune.

00:02:07.999 --> 00:02:12.999
Soon the Stock Exchange Council
purchased land in Drašković Street

00:02:12.999 --> 00:02:17.999
and invited six top architects
to submit their designs.

00:02:19.800 --> 00:02:22.999
The palace should
have an imposing exterior

00:02:22.999 --> 00:02:24.999
without unnecessary ornamentation

00:02:24.999 --> 00:02:28.999
so that its serious and solid
design fits into the neighbourhood

00:02:29.000 --> 00:02:34.999
which will become the city's
commercial and trading centre,

00:02:34.999 --> 00:02:37.000
specified the invitation
to submit bids.

00:02:37.480 --> 00:02:40.999
After long deliberation, the jury
decided to give the project

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:45.480
to the creative and professionally
very daring architect Viktor Kovačić.

00:02:45.800 --> 00:02:48.999
Kovačić not only provided an
outstanding design for the palace,

00:02:48.999 --> 00:02:51.999
but was also the only candidate

00:02:51.999 --> 00:02:56.960
who submitted the design for
the entrance to the new part of the city.

00:02:56.999 --> 00:03:01.160
He approached every task
in an individual manner,

00:03:01.640 --> 00:03:06.800
without repeating any element
from any previous design projects.

00:03:06.999 --> 00:03:12.999
ALEKSANDER LASLO
architectural engineer

00:03:12.999 --> 00:03:17.800
The main theme
in this case was an idea

00:03:17.999 --> 00:03:23.999
which could be defined as
an insistence on excellence.

00:03:25.640 --> 00:03:29.000
This is why he is considered

00:03:30.320 --> 00:03:34.999
the founder of
the Zagreb School of Architecture.

00:03:36.999 --> 00:03:40.999
Kovačić was a genius from Hum on
Sutla and Otto Wagner's student.

00:03:40.999 --> 00:03:42.999
Before the project
for the Stock Exchange Palace,

00:03:43.160 --> 00:03:46.640
he had mostly designed family
homes and blocks of flats.

00:03:46.999 --> 00:03:50.640
He had only one
monumental project:

00:03:50.999 --> 00:03:53.000
The Parish Church of Saint Blaise.

00:03:53.480 --> 00:03:58.800
Kovačić showed a strange tenacity

00:03:58.999 --> 00:04:02.800
when he decided to devote
himself to the city of Zagreb.

00:04:02.999 --> 00:04:09.999
The building was controversial due
to its seemingly retrograde facade,

00:04:09.999 --> 00:04:11.999
which is neoclassical.

00:04:11.999 --> 00:04:17.320
However, if you look
at its spatial organisation

00:04:17.800 --> 00:04:22.999
and the elements of its construction,
the building is truly modernist.

00:04:23.999 --> 00:04:29.999
Work started in 1923, but
since Kovačić died a year later,

00:04:29.999 --> 00:04:34.999
the supervision of the project
was taken over by Hugo Ehrlich.

00:04:35.000 --> 00:04:43.999
I would call it a virtuoso
composition in the third dimension.

00:04:43.999 --> 00:04:47.999
When you analyse the main
cross-section of the building,

00:04:47.999 --> 00:04:54.999
when you notice the manipulation
of heights, levels and floors,

00:04:54.999 --> 00:05:02.999
the skill as well as the brilliant
purity of the spatial organisation,

00:05:03.000 --> 00:05:08.480
you realise that the building remains
almost unsurpassed even today.

00:05:08.999 --> 00:05:12.160
The detailed documents illustrate
the capabilities of the suppliers

00:05:12.800 --> 00:05:15.999
operating at
the time of construction.

00:05:15.999 --> 00:05:19.999
The investors checked
a wide range of offers

00:05:19.999 --> 00:05:23.999
in order to find the best materials
and the most up-to-date equipment,

00:05:24.160 --> 00:05:27.999
from special scales
and vaults to safe boxes.

00:05:45.999 --> 00:05:48.999
The communication equipment
is something worth mentioning.

00:05:48.999 --> 00:05:52.640
Internal communication equipment
was installed in all the major offices.

00:05:52.999 --> 00:05:57.999
A telephone exchange enabled
simultaneous use by multiple users.

00:05:57.999 --> 00:06:00.999
It was so successful that
the consulate in Switzerland

00:06:00.999 --> 00:06:03.999
was asked to find out more about
it at the Zurich Stock Exchange.

00:06:03.999 --> 00:06:06.999
However, construction work did
not progress according to the plan,

00:06:06.999 --> 00:06:09.999
and many contractors blamed
each other for the delays.

00:06:09.999 --> 00:06:12.999
This way they stood to lose
the money they had paid

00:06:12.999 --> 00:06:15.999
as a guarantee for
timely completion.

00:06:15.999 --> 00:06:24.960
It takes six times longer
to put the stone blocks in place,

00:06:24.999 --> 00:06:29.999
complained constructors from
Skopal, Juričić and Batušić.

00:06:29.999 --> 00:06:32.320
They put the blame
on the supplier of stone blocks

00:06:32.640 --> 00:06:37.999
and asked to change the procedure
and get compensated for lost time.

00:06:38.999 --> 00:06:42.999
The Stock Exchange shareholders
wanted the building to stand out.

00:06:42.999 --> 00:06:45.999
They ordered
custom-designed furniture

00:06:45.999 --> 00:06:49.999
to demonstrate the strength
and stability of the institution.

00:07:08.999 --> 00:07:13.999
The ambitions plans were finalised
a couple of months before the start

00:07:13.999 --> 00:07:15.999
of an unprecedented
global financial crisis,

00:07:15.999 --> 00:07:18.999
and they almost ended
in complete failure.

00:07:18.999 --> 00:07:25.999
As long as we hoped to cover the
cost of the palace construction,

00:07:25.999 --> 00:07:28.999
we did not turn for help
to anyone, they wrote.

00:07:29.000 --> 00:07:31.160
The shareholders
appealed to the directors

00:07:31.640 --> 00:07:33.960
of the First Croatian Savings Bank,

00:07:33.999 --> 00:07:36.999
the Croatian Discount Bank
and five more large banks.

00:07:36.999 --> 00:07:39.999
To complete the palace, they
needed another ten million dinars,

00:07:39.999 --> 00:07:41.999
in addition to the five million

00:07:41.999 --> 00:07:45.320
they were hoping to borrow
interest-free from the government.

00:07:46.999 --> 00:07:51.999
The banks were luckily
willing to give them a loan

00:07:51.999 --> 00:07:57.999
and the new Stock Exchange was
opened on Saturday, 18 June 1927.

00:07:58.999 --> 00:08:01.999
The dignitaries who
walked into this lobby

00:08:01.999 --> 00:08:06.999
to the applause of the stock
exchange brokers and members

00:08:07.320 --> 00:08:10.999
included representatives of the
stock exchanges from Vienna,

00:08:10.999 --> 00:08:15.999
Prague, Budapest, Ljubljana,
Novi Sad and Belgrade,

00:08:15.999 --> 00:08:21.999
government and church officials,
and a delegation from Belgrade

00:08:22.160 --> 00:08:25.999
including the King's emissary,
Army General Marković,

00:08:25.999 --> 00:08:29.999
and the Minister
of Finance Dr Spaho.

00:08:31.999 --> 00:08:36.999
Due to its reputation abroad and the
authority of its arbitration tribunal,

00:08:37.320 --> 00:08:39.999
our stock exchange has
become an important institution

00:08:39.999 --> 00:08:42.999
not only in the city of Zagreb,
but in the entire Kingdom,

00:08:42.999 --> 00:08:47.160
said the Stock Exchange
President, Dr Stanko Šverljuga.

00:08:49.999 --> 00:08:52.999
According to the program
for the opening ceremony,

00:08:52.999 --> 00:08:55.999
we know that the gallery
was reserved for ladies,

00:08:55.999 --> 00:08:59.800
and that there was a formal
lunch at the Esplanade Hotel.

00:09:01.640 --> 00:09:05.640
Visitors were not only impressed
by the palace's architecture

00:09:05.999 --> 00:09:08.000
as the palace had its
own telephone exchange,

00:09:08.480 --> 00:09:12.999
electricity transformer station,
library, reading room, post office,

00:09:12.999 --> 00:09:15.999
printing works offices,
restaurant and a doctor.

00:09:15.999 --> 00:09:20.999
The palace also had central heating
and was partially air conditioned.

00:09:21.800 --> 00:09:24.999
The guests left, and,
on the following Monday,

00:09:24.999 --> 00:09:27.999
the offices were put into use
by stock exchange brokers.

00:09:27.999 --> 00:09:30.999
There were not
many brokers at the time:

00:09:30.999 --> 00:09:33.999
only about ten dealing in securities
and even fewer in commodities.

00:09:34.480 --> 00:09:36.999
It was not necessary
to have more brokers

00:09:36.999 --> 00:09:39.999
since the stock exchange members
could call out bids themselves here.

00:09:39.999 --> 00:09:44.640
Brokers needed to be involved
only in closing transactions.

00:09:44.999 --> 00:09:48.999
Trading would start every working
day at noon, lasting for an hour.

00:09:48.999 --> 00:09:52.960
It was made easier
by the latest technology:

00:09:52.999 --> 00:09:57.999
there were 52 telephone
booths with light signals in the hall,

00:09:58.160 --> 00:10:02.999
which enabled the brokers to
receive instruction from their clients.

00:10:02.999 --> 00:10:04.999
A number of booths
were also used by banks

00:10:04.999 --> 00:10:07.960
to communicate directly
with the Stock Exchange.

00:10:07.999 --> 00:10:09.640
The hall had a clock

00:10:09.999 --> 00:10:12.999
that was automatically aligned with
all the other clocks in the building:

00:10:12.999 --> 00:10:15.999
time was literally money here!

00:10:17.999 --> 00:10:22.960
The hall is topped by a double
dome ensuring excellent acoustics.

00:10:22.999 --> 00:10:26.999
The space between the inner and
the outer dome provided insulation

00:10:26.999 --> 00:10:32.640
and the ventilation openings gave
air to the often heated atmosphere.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:39.960
The Great Depression was
not felt in the country in 1929,

00:10:39.999 --> 00:10:42.999
but there was a political crisis then.

00:10:42.999 --> 00:10:47.999
The economic crisis started
only in the autumn of 1931,

00:10:47.999 --> 00:10:51.999
with the collapse of the
First Croatian Savings Bank.

00:10:51.999 --> 00:10:55.999
Commissioners were appointed to
head all the monetary institutions,

00:10:55.999 --> 00:10:59.999
including the Zagreb Stock
Exchange which continued working.

00:10:59.999 --> 00:11:03.999
Activities were, however, reduced

00:11:03.999 --> 00:11:08.999
and it was not allowed
to trade in foreign exchange,

00:11:08.999 --> 00:11:12.999
but it helped the country
get out of the crisis

00:11:12.999 --> 00:11:17.640
as the employees
spoke German well,

00:11:17.999 --> 00:11:24.999
and thus helped Yugoslavia enter
trading agreements with Germany.

00:11:24.999 --> 00:11:27.999
This happened in 1934

00:11:27.999 --> 00:11:33.800
when the Third Reich started
purchasing all the market surpluses

00:11:33.999 --> 00:11:36.999
produced in Yugoslavia.

00:11:36.999 --> 00:11:41.999
The stock exchange listed about 20
monetary institutions, companies

00:11:41.999 --> 00:11:45.999
which were top players in the
Croatian economy at the time.

00:11:45.999 --> 00:11:49.999
Among the most traded stocks
were those of the Isis company

00:11:49.999 --> 00:11:52.999
- a joint stock company
for drugs and chemicals,

00:11:52.999 --> 00:11:55.800
the Slavonija Timber company, the
Dubrovnik Steamship Navigation

00:11:55.999 --> 00:11:59.000
and the Adriatic Hotels and Resorts
company of Sušak.

00:11:59.480 --> 00:12:01.999
Once a transaction was closed,

00:12:02.000 --> 00:12:05.999
the traded securities were brought
from the vaults below the hall.

00:12:05.999 --> 00:12:08.999
The Gremial Hall was where
the last checks were performed.

00:12:08.999 --> 00:12:12.999
Later on, the counting
office was located in the hall,

00:12:12.999 --> 00:12:16.999
and today it is used by
specialists looking for forgeries.

00:12:17.999 --> 00:12:19.999
This is the Commodity
Exchange Hall.

00:12:19.999 --> 00:12:23.999
The commodities traded here
included eggs from Croatia,

00:12:23.999 --> 00:12:26.999
Bosnia and Steiermark
and coffee from Costa Rica,

00:12:26.999 --> 00:12:30.960
Guatemala, Columbia
and many other countries.

00:12:30.999 --> 00:12:35.999
The 1926 trading list also included

00:12:35.999 --> 00:12:45.999
soap, prunes, lard, marmalade,
blue vitriol, and even petrol.

00:12:48.999 --> 00:12:53.999
The Zagreb Stock Exchange was
very proud of its arbitration tribunal

00:12:53.999 --> 00:12:57.999
which business people would turn
to rather than to the state courts.

00:12:58.000 --> 00:13:01.999
The tribunal held its session in this
hall, known today as the Horseshoe

00:13:01.999 --> 00:13:07.960
below the slogan Law and
Justice etched into this plate.

00:13:08.999 --> 00:13:10.999
In December 1931,

00:13:10.999 --> 00:13:13.999
the arbitration tribunal heard
the case of the Croatian Bank

00:13:13.999 --> 00:13:16.999
which sued the Credit
Institution of Ljubljana for refusing

00:13:16.999 --> 00:13:19.800
to recognise and
settle a transaction

00:13:19.999 --> 00:13:21.999
related to 4,000
war-damage bonds.

00:13:22.320 --> 00:13:26.999
The case was unanimously ruled
in favour of the Croatian Bank.

00:13:27.999 --> 00:13:29.800
The Stock Exchange was managed

00:13:29.999 --> 00:13:31.999
by the Zagreb Stocks
and Commodities Council

00:13:31.999 --> 00:13:34.999
whose sessions were
held in this hall.

00:13:34.999 --> 00:13:37.999
The Council was authorised
to issue licenses to brokers,

00:13:37.999 --> 00:13:41.640
appoint the commission
responsible for exchange rates,

00:13:41.960 --> 00:13:44.999
approve the listing of new shares

00:13:44.999 --> 00:13:46.999
and generally run the Stock
Exchange operations. Today,

00:13:46.999 --> 00:13:49.999
this is where the Croatian National
Bank Council holds its meetings.

00:13:49.999 --> 00:13:52.999
The Council is the highest authority
in the Croatian National Bank

00:13:52.999 --> 00:13:55.999
and it is headed by the
Governor of the Bank.

00:13:55.999 --> 00:13:57.999
The Great Depression
was not the only issue

00:13:57.999 --> 00:14:00.999
worrying the Zagreb Stock
Exchange Council in the late 1920s.

00:14:00.999 --> 00:14:02.999
Competitors from Belgrade,

00:14:02.999 --> 00:14:05.999
supported by the
King's minister Kumandi,

00:14:05.999 --> 00:14:08.999
wanted to find a way to close
down the Zagreb Stock Exchange

00:14:08.999 --> 00:14:10.999
and merge it with the
exchange in Belgrade.

00:14:11.000 --> 00:14:13.999
The minutes of the meetings of the
Stock Exchange managing board

00:14:13.999 --> 00:14:15.999
make up for a very interesting read.

00:14:15.999 --> 00:14:20.160
At the session held on 21 March
1928, certain listings were deleted,

00:14:20.640 --> 00:14:22.999
new ones were added,
and it was also decided

00:14:22.999 --> 00:14:25.320
that the Stock Exchange
would donate 1000 dinars

00:14:25.640 --> 00:14:27.999
for the erection of
a statue of King Tomislav.

00:14:27.999 --> 00:14:29.999
Many other requests
for donations were rejected,

00:14:29.999 --> 00:14:32.999
and master Kordić was
granted a 50% discount on his rent

00:14:32.999 --> 00:14:36.999
for the first semester due to illness.

00:14:38.000 --> 00:14:41.480
All this was witnessed
by the Stock Exchange Secretary,

00:14:41.800 --> 00:14:45.800
who lived in a luxury
flat in the building.

00:14:45.999 --> 00:14:47.999
The start of the Second World War

00:14:47.999 --> 00:14:50.480
coincided with a further
reduction in trading activities.

00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:52.999
And in 1942

00:14:52.999 --> 00:14:56.999
the building was forcefully
"rented" to the Ministry of Justice.

00:14:59.320 --> 00:15:03.999
The end of the war also saw
the end of the Stock Exchange.

00:15:04.480 --> 00:15:07.640
The Yugoslav communist
regime closed the Stock Exchange,

00:15:07.999 --> 00:15:11.160
seized its property
and laid off its employees.

00:15:11.999 --> 00:15:15.999
Since the Zagreb Stock
Exchange is no longer in operation,

00:15:15.999 --> 00:15:17.999
I have to relieve you of your duties,

00:15:17.999 --> 00:15:22.320
wrote Eugen Senji, the provisional
receiver of the confiscated assets,

00:15:22.640 --> 00:15:24.999
to Stjepan Fritz, the treasurer.

00:15:24.999 --> 00:15:27.480
The building was soon overtaken

00:15:27.800 --> 00:15:29.999
by a branch office of the
National Bank of Yugoslavia

00:15:29.999 --> 00:15:32.999
and the Social Accounting Service.

00:15:33.999 --> 00:15:36.320
Upon the independence
of the Republic of Croatia,

00:15:36.800 --> 00:15:39.999
the building of the former Stock
and Commodity Exchange

00:15:39.999 --> 00:15:43.999
became the home to one of the
most important state institutions,

00:15:43.999 --> 00:15:45.999
the Croatian National Bank.

00:15:45.999 --> 00:15:49.800
The claws that once symbolised the
strength of the Croatian economy

00:15:49.999 --> 00:15:52.999
are today in the service
of the stability of the kuna.

00:16:02.999 --> 00:16:07.999
The Croatian National Bank was
established on 23 December 1991,

00:16:07.999 --> 00:16:11.800
and the provisional
currency, the Croatian dinar,

00:16:11.999 --> 00:16:13.999
entered circulation
on the same day.

00:16:13.999 --> 00:16:18.999
Once inflation was put under control
by the 1993 Stabilisation Programme,

00:16:18.999 --> 00:16:23.999
the kuna was introduced
as currency on 30 May 1994.

00:16:25.999 --> 00:16:28.999
The Croatian National Bank
is an independent state institution,

00:16:28.999 --> 00:16:30.999
and its main goal is price stability.

00:16:31.160 --> 00:16:33.999
It defines monetary
and foreign exchange policy,

00:16:33.999 --> 00:16:37.960
manages the foreign exchange
reserves, issues banknotes

00:16:37.999 --> 00:16:40.999
as well as coins, and
supervises the credit institutions

00:16:40.999 --> 00:16:43.640
and payment
operations in the country.

00:16:43.960 --> 00:16:45.960
The work and
expertise of its employees

00:16:45.999 --> 00:16:48.999
have made it
a modern central bank

00:16:48.999 --> 00:16:52.960
operating in accordance with
the standards of the European Union.

